      <p class="page-subtitle"></p>
      <div class="prose"><h2>The Power of Small Moments</h2>
<p>The best essays are rarely about the championship game or the mission trip. They are about <strong>small moments</strong>: a conversation that shifted your thinking, a quiet decision nobody else saw, or noticing a pattern in your own behavior.</p>
<p><strong>The smaller the moment, the bigger the insight.</strong></p>
<h2>The Reality Check</h2>
<p>Most students panic because they think they lack "material." They are usually looking through the wrong lens.</p>
<p><strong>The Myth:</strong> "I need a tragedy or a massive accomplishment."</p>
<p><strong>The Reality:</strong> You need <strong>friction</strong>. Look for a moment where you felt confused, challenged, or surprised.</p>
<p><strong>The Myth:</strong> "I need to sound smart or heroic."</p>
<p><strong>The Reality:</strong> You need to sound <strong>honest</strong>. Admissions officers can smell a "performance" from a mile away.</p>
<p><strong>The Myth:</strong> "I need a story with a perfect happy ending."</p>
<p><strong>The Reality:</strong> You need a story that is <strong>yours</strong>. Unresolved endings are often more interesting than perfect ones.</p>
<h2>The "Zoom-In" Exercise</h2>
<p>Don't brainstorm "topics." Brainstorm <strong>scenes</strong>. Close your eyes and run your memory like a movie. Where does the camera zoom in?</p>
<h3>Work</h3>
<ul>
<li>⛔ <strong>Wide Shot:</strong> "My job at the coffee shop." (Too big. No detail.)</li>
<li>✅ <strong>Zoom In:</strong> "The morning a regular customer snapped at me for getting her order wrong, and I realized I'd been going through the motions for weeks."</li>
</ul>
<h3>Skills</h3>
<ul>
<li>⛔ <strong>Wide Shot:</strong> "Learning to play guitar." (Generic.)</li>
<li>✅ <strong>Zoom In:</strong> "The specific night my fingers finally hurt <em>less</em> than my desire to play, and I understood what my teacher meant by 'muscle memory'."</li>
</ul>
<h3>Leadership</h3>
<ul>
<li>⛔ <strong>Wide Shot:</strong> "Being Debate Captain." (Resume item.)</li>
<li>✅ <strong>Zoom In:</strong> "The 30 seconds of silence before I decided to enforce a rule against my friend."</li>
</ul>
